      "review_summary": "The PR adds `externalContent` provenance to plugin hook types, before_tool_call events and contexts, trusted tool policies, embedded-runner prompt/tool-result propagation, docs, tests, and plugin SDK surface budgets.\n\nPR surface: Source +200, Tests +163, Docs +40, Other 0. Total +403 across 15 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. The detector reads `Source:` labels from `value.split(\"---\")[0]` for the whole string, so a prefix separator or multiple wrapped blocks can produce wrong or incomplete provenance without needing a full runtime run to see the flaw.",
